name: Jimmy Dean Southwestern Sausage Tarts
author: JimmyDean
summary: A snap to make, these Southwest-style egg, sausage, Cheddar, and salsa tarts are perfect for brunch or as party appetizers.
ingredients: 1 (16 ounce) package Regular Flavor Jimmy Dean Pork Sausage, cooked, crumbled and drained
directions: Unwrap piecrusts and roll each out to slightly thinner than original thickness
Use a 4-inch cookie cutter to cut circles out of crust; gently press each circle into bottom and up the sides of ungreased muffin cup baking pans (crust will not reach top of tin)
If necessary, re-roll dough scraps to make additional dough circles
Combine cooked sausage with remaining ingredients; mix well
Spoon mixture into each crust, filling about 3/4 full
Bake 40 minutes or until crust is browned
